Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF96FF9DC65DF95EFE79F905" box="[263,469,1685,1706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hunanens">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF96FF9DC65DF95EFE79F905" box="[263,469,1685,1706]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cardamine hunanens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is is easily distinguished from the related 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF96FF9DC436F95EFC5DF905" box="[876,1009,1685,1706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lihengiana">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF96FF9DC436F95EFC5DF905" box="[876,1009,1685,1706]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">C. lihengiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 3- or 5-foliolate (vs. simple) basal and lowermost cauline leaves and purple to violet (vs. white) petals 5–7 (vs. 3.5–4.5) mm long.
</paragraph>
