<subSubSection id="C3266576FF95FF9EC7E7FF54FA8CFEC4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8336FDFF95FF9EC7E7FF54FA8CFEC4" blockId="3.[136,1452,159,363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF95FF9EC7E7FF54FE93FF18" bold="true" box="[189,319,159,183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF95FF9EC603FF54FDE1FF18" box="[345,589,159,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hunanensis">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF95FF9EC603FF54FDE1FF18" box="[345,589,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cardamine hunanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known thus far only from Yizhang Xian (
<collectingRegion id="49F8F81FFF95FF9EC33FFF54FABAFF18" box="[1125,1302,159,183]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Hunan Province</collectingRegion>
), most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF95FF9EC7A0FF0FFE20FF74" box="[250,396,195,219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lihengiana">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF95FF9EC7A0FF0FFE20FF74" box="[250,396,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">C. lihengiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Yiliang Xian (
<collectingRegion id="49F8F81FFF95FF9EC513FF08FD0CFF74" box="[585,672,195,219]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
), and the two xians (counties) are separated by a distance of some 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC235FF08FF01FF50" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.385" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="km" value="1385.0">1,385 km</quantity>
. From the latter, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF95FF9EC63AFF23FE5AFF50" box="[352,502,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hunanensis">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF95FF9EC63AFF23FE5AFF50" box="[352,502,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">C. hunanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished by being non-stoloniferous and by having 3–5-foliolate basal and lowermost cauline leaves; purple to violet petals 5–7 × 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC58EFEC0FC83FE8C" box="[724,815,267,291]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
, fruiting pedicels 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC4B7FEC0FBC9FE8C" box="[1005,1125,267,291]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 cm</quantity>
long, sepals 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC3B5FEC0FAC2FE8C" box="[1263,1390,267,291]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5999999999999996" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="2.5999999999999996" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.8 mm</quantity>
long, and styles 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC7A0FEE4FEFEFEE8" box="[250,338,303,327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
long. By contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D7EFF95FF9EC545FEFBFD1DFEE8" box="[543,689,303,327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lihengiana">
<emphasis id="B948EAEFFF95FF9EC545FEFBFD1DFEE8" box="[543,689,303,327]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">C. lihengiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stoloniferous with simple basal and lowermost cauline leaves, white petals 3.5–4.5 × 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC663FE98FE04FEC4" box="[313,424,339,363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
, fruiting pedicels 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC532FE98FD67FEC4" box="[616,715,339,363]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3 cm</quantity>
long, sepals 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC40CFE98FC7AFEC4" box="[854,982,339,363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
long, and styles 
<quantity id="4CC49B18FF95FF9EC3D0FE98FB4EFEC4" box="[1162,1250,339,363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
